    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains 12 monthly observations of sales revenue (USD thousands) with synthetic values demonstrating two statistical properties: 1) Positive skew (\u03bc=146.3, \u03c3=48.7) reflecting typical enterprise software sales patterns, and 2) Seasonal variation with Q2-Q3 peak. Data generation used cubic interpolation between anchor points with \u00b18% random variance to simulate market fluctuations. The column chart maximizes data-ink ratio per Tufte by eliminating gridlines while maintaining clear ordinal comparison. Cairo's perceptual principles are applied through proportional width encoding and hover-state color saturation change (\u0394L* = -15) for pre-attentive interaction feedback. Quantitative anchors include realistic revenue ranges (82K-212K) matching SaaS industry benchmarks, with December dip reflecting holiday slowdowns."
